{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-page-press-release-tsx","path":"/media-center/wise-paris-forum-explores-'education-futures-fostering-learning-societies'","result":{"data":{"contentfulPagePressRelease":{"id":"4f485700-0888-563b-b077-872ca63491ae","slug":"wise-paris-forum-explores-'education-futures-fostering-learning-societies'","title":"WISE@Paris Forum Explores ‘Education Futures: Fostering Learning Societies’","date":"2019-02-21","filterTags":null,"filterEntity":[{"contentful_id":"5QvNeD8VK84AwEaWOUUEYe"}],"heroImage":null,"modulesWrapper":[{"modules":[{"__typename":"ContentfulModuleBodyText","id":"1347e303-2213-5bd0-951f-400101bc9b9a","text":{"childMarkdownRemark":{"html":"<p>The World Innovation Summit for Education (WISE), an initiative of Qatar Foundation (QF), has hosted its sixth regional forum, WISE@Paris, under the theme ‘Education Futures: Fostering Learning Societies.’ The event, which took place from February 20-21, was held under the high patronage of Mr. Emmanuel Macron, President of France.</p>"}}},{"__typename":"ContentfulModuleImageGallery","id":"7c9b354c-985e-52b1-9614-5306b0d0943e","images":[{"caption":null,"image":{"id":"af69802c-27d8-573d-9399-7d8ba500ac02","title":"Image3","file":{"details":{"image":{"width":1200,"height":1600}}},"sizes":{"aspectRatio":1.8666666666666667,"src":"//images.ctfassets.net/2h1qowfuxkq7/2bzVwdnjgyxY9Dc9bAecGe/99659924274afce0e7acb0bbafb1851e/Image3.jpg?w=1120&h=600&q=85","srcSet":"//images.ctfassets.net/2h1qowfuxkq7/2bzVwdnjgyxY9Dc9bAecGe/99659924274afce0e7acb0bbafb1851e/Image3.jpg?w=280&h=150&q=85 280w,\n//images.ctfassets.net/2h1qowfuxkq7/2bzVwdnjgyxY9Dc9bAecGe/99659924274afce0e7acb0bbafb1851e/Image3.jpg?w=560&h=300&q=85 560w,\n//images.ctfassets.net/2h1qowfuxkq7/2bzVwdnjgyxY9Dc9bAecGe/99659924274afce0e7acb0bbafb1851e/Image3.jpg?w=1120&h=600&q=85 1120w,\n//images.ctfassets.net/2h1qowfuxkq7/2bzVwdnjgyxY9Dc9bAecGe/99659924274afce0e7acb0bbafb1851e/Image3.jpg?w=1200&h=643&q=85 1200w","srcWebp":"//images.ctfassets.net/2h1qowfuxkq7/2bzVwdnjgyxY9Dc9bAecGe/99659924274afce0e7acb0bbafb1851e/Image3.jpg?w=1120&h=600&q=85&fm=webp","srcSetWebp":"//images.ctfassets.net/2h1qowfuxkq7/2bzVwdnjgyxY9Dc9bAecGe/99659924274afce0e7acb0bbafb1851e/Image3.jpg?w=280&h=150&q=85&fm=webp 280w,\n//images.ctfassets.net/2h1qowfuxkq7/2bzVwdnjgyxY9Dc9bAecGe/99659924274afce0e7acb0bbafb1851e/Image3.jpg?w=560&h=300&q=85&fm=webp 560w,\n//images.ctfassets.net/2h1qowfuxkq7/2bzVwdnjgyxY9Dc9bAecGe/99659924274afce0e7acb0bbafb1851e/Image3.jpg?w=1120&h=600&q=85&fm=webp 1120w,\n//images.ctfassets.net/2h1qowfuxkq7/2bzVwdnjgyxY9Dc9bAecGe/99659924274afce0e7acb0bbafb1851e/Image3.jpg?w=1200&h=643&q=85&fm=webp 1200w","sizes":"(max-width: 1120px) 100vw, 1120px"},"singleMode":{"aspectRatio":1.7906976744186047,"src":"//images.ctfassets.net/2h1qowfuxkq7/2bzVwdnjgyxY9Dc9bAecGe/99659924274afce0e7acb0bbafb1851e/Image3.jpg?w=1540&h=860&q=85&fit=pad","srcSet":"//images.ctfassets.net/2h1qowfuxkq7/2bzVwdnjgyxY9Dc9bAecGe/99659924274afce0e7acb0bbafb1851e/Image3.jpg?w=385&h=215&q=85&fit=pad 385w,\n//images.ctfassets.net/2h1qowfuxkq7/2bzVwdnjgyxY9Dc9bAecGe/99659924274afce0e7acb0bbafb1851e/Image3.jpg?w=770&h=430&q=85&fit=pad 770w,\n//images.ctfassets.net/2h1qowfuxkq7/2bzVwdnjgyxY9Dc9bAecGe/99659924274afce0e7acb0bbafb1851e/Image3.jpg?w=1200&h=670&q=85&fit=pad 1200w","srcWebp":"//images.ctfassets.net/2h1qowfuxkq7/2bzVwdnjgyxY9Dc9bAecGe/99659924274afce0e7acb0bbafb1851e/Image3.jpg?w=1540&h=860&q=85&fm=webp&fit=pad","srcSetWebp":"//images.ctfassets.net/2h1qowfuxkq7/2bzVwdnjgyxY9Dc9bAecGe/99659924274afce0e7acb0bbafb1851e/Image3.jpg?w=385&h=215&q=85&fm=webp&fit=pad 385w,\n//images.ctfassets.net/2h1qowfuxkq7/2bzVwdnjgyxY9Dc9bAecGe/99659924274afce0e7acb0bbafb1851e/Image3.jpg?w=770&h=430&q=85&fm=webp&fit=pad 770w,\n//images.ctfassets.net/2h1qowfuxkq7/2bzVwdnjgyxY9Dc9bAecGe/99659924274afce0e7acb0bbafb1851e/Image3.jpg?w=1200&h=670&q=85&fm=webp&fit=pad 1200w","sizes":"(max-width: 1540px) 100vw, 1540px"}}}]},{"__typename":"ContentfulModuleBodyText","id":"c7ea6992-b568-55a4-93b6-967b81c05656","text":{"childMarkdownRemark":{"html":"<p>WISE@Paris gathered over 800 local and international thought leaders, practitioners, innovators, and media representatives to discuss and foster the learning societies of today and tomorrow, with the forum also seeing the theme for the next edition of the WISE Summit – to be held in Doha in November – being unveiled.</p>\n<p>On the first day of WISE@Paris, participants had the opportunity to create their own learning journey by joining discussions and interactive sessions around the future of learning at various venues in Paris. These sessions were organized by WISE and its partners, including the Center for Research and Interdisciplinarity, the United Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization (UNESCO), Education Above All, Sciences Po, and Pixis and Ashoka from Station F – the world’s largest startup campus.</p>"}}},{"__typename":"ContentfulModuleQuote","id":"11eeefe9-5071-5a75-8c42-002e31f18131","quote":{"quote":"WISE is a response to the necessity of revitalizing education and providing a global platform for the development of new ideas and solutions. It has evolved into a thriving global, multi-sectoral community, which continues to generate fruitful dialogue and productive partnerships","childMarkdownRemark":{"html":"<p>WISE is a response to the necessity of revitalizing education and providing a global platform for the development of new ideas and solutions. It has evolved into a thriving global, multi-sectoral community, which continues to generate fruitful dialogue and productive partnerships</p>"}},"author":" ","title":" ","useCompactDesign":true,"quoteOnRightSide":null},{"__typename":"ContentfulModuleBodyText","id":"25646e62-5fe5-57d8-93f2-922314a260e3","text":{"childMarkdownRemark":{"html":"<p>The second day of the forum, held at Palais de Tokyo, featured an engaging set up of formats that allowed topics such as ‘Rethinking K-12 Education’, ‘Empowering Teachers and Education Leaders’, ‘Decrypting the Future of Work’, and ‘Cultivating Global Citizenship’, to be explored through a variety of interactive experiences and discussions.</p>\n<p>Omran Al-Kuwari, Chief Executive Officer, Qatar Foundation International, delivered the keynote speech on the second day of WISE@Paris.</p>\n<p>“WISE is a response to the necessity of revitalizing education and providing a global platform for the development of new ideas and solutions. It has evolved into a thriving global, multi-sectoral community, which continues to generate fruitful dialogue and productive partnerships,” Mr. Al-Kuwari said.</p>\n<p>“WISE@ events are local and regional education conferences that take place between WISE’s biennial global summits. The successful model of the WISE Summit has been adapted to create engagement activities that take place over one to two days, using the convening expertise of WISE and its access to a broad global community of experts in education. With the support of local partners, we have been able to take WISE on the road.”</p>\n<p>Additional WISE@Paris speakers included Dr. Maggie Aderin-Pocock MBE, a space scientist and co-presenter of the BBC program The Sky At Night, and Mr. Nicolas Sadirac, Founder of 42, a private, nonprofit and tuition-free computer programming school. </p>"}}},{"__typename":"ContentfulModuleImageGallery","id":"448a673a-5229-5d06-8c3e-f617185310d6","images":[{"caption":null,"image":{"id":"a17932f0-0d60-593e-a04f-e5fd13f47596","title":"Image2","file":{"details":{"image":{"width":2046,"height":1978}}},"sizes":{"aspectRatio":1.8666666666666667,"src":"//images.ctfassets.net/2h1qowfuxkq7/81W23XgOflaRNyrMxvTme/8b70a444c205833c2df5b39453c53b7f/Image2.jpg?w=1120&h=600&q=85","srcSet":"//images.ctfassets.net/2h1qowfuxkq7/81W23XgOflaRNyrMxvTme/8b70a444c205833c2df5b39453c53b7f/Image2.jpg?w=280&h=150&q=85 280w,\n//images.ctfassets.net/2h1qowfuxkq7/81W23XgOflaRNyrMxvTme/8b70a444c205833c2df5b39453c53b7f/Image2.jpg?w=5